9d0f4d-7e30-785a-8535-befb294140a0","time_text":"03:21:00","competitive":true,"course_rank":5,"status_code":"OK","affiliations":[{"label":"COC"}],"outcome_text":"03:21:00","overall_rank":5,"result_notes":null,"category_name":"3 Hour Group","category_rank":5,"individual_id":null,"metric_summary":"Penalty 420; Points 400; Total Time 0","competitor_name":"Lee Phipps Group","competitor_type":"team","additional_course":false,"affiliation_labels":["COC"]}],"course_id":"019d0f4d-7e57-7c91-8d42-338cd3c8e1a5","course_name":"Overall","distance_km":null,"result_count":5,"control_count":null,"course_climb_m":null}],"event_id":"019b81f3-1f4e-77df-adf3-7b2c0f2f8249","venue_id":"019b7b2f-bf4b-7d04-bb73-a3e7756e878a","event_date":"2017-05-14","event_kind":"race","event_name":"Ultimate Series #7 - Score O","venue_name":"Teanaway Forks","event_notes":null,"course_count":8,"event_status":null,"result_count":55,"citation_count":3,"event_comments":"Ultimate Series #6 (Pig War) – Classic – Lick Creek\nThank you to all of our volunteers this weekend!\n\nDownload and print the Teanaway Weekend info doc.\nThe Ultimate Orienteer series is the sampler pack of orienteering: each event gives you the opportunity to try a different flavor!\nThe seventh event in the series is: SCORE-O!\nAt a score-o, you can find controls in any order and earn points for each control you find within the time limit. Controls are assigned points based on navigational difficulty and distance: easy controls might be worth 10 or 20 points, while difficult controls could be worth 100 points. The challenge is to decide which controls you can visit within the time limit that will earn the most points. You’ll lose points if you return late, so keep an eye on your watch!\nWhile the terrain is rugged and navigationally challenging, the format of a score-o is beginner-friendly since you control (pun intended) the difficulty of every control simply by choosing which to find. And, if you have trouble finding a control, you can skip it and move on!\nPro Tips: it is handy to have a highlighter or other writing utensil at the start of the race, so that you can mark your intended route. Also, don’t forget to wear a watch so that you know when to return to the finish!\nCareful course planning, keeping your eye on the clock, and staying located are all key to success in the Teanaway Forks Score O. Even experts will have trouble visiting every control in the given time limit. Pick a route that best uses your time: maybe that means maximizing points in a short distance, or maybe you want to explore a new area and visit some controls along the way, it’s up to you!\nMost controls are shared across the two courses, but you may find controls not marked on your map. There will be some water out on the course, but please carry what you need.\nVegetation coloring on the map can be used as general guidelines but has changed enough that your navigation should rely on contours, major trails, and rocky features. With the wet winter, most marshy areas are more like lakes, and many water courses are much more swollen than the map may lead you to believe. Trails in flat and/or low areas also sometimes have large patches of water, expect to get your feet wet a couple times, but you’ll dry quickly in the Central Washington sun. Be careful of footing in areas with scattered trees: old fallen logs may be soft or firm and can hide holes. You may also encounter an area with recent thinning (freshly cut smaller trees) that can be navigated through without too much trouble.\nBrush piles (brown circle with dot) are mostly to be ignored although some do still exist and some can be more accurately identified as knolls. Smaller trails may be hard to spy unless you’re standing right on them, especially the trails marked as indistinct (two dashes with a larger gap). When venturing cross-country, you may find a few un-mapped trails. Do your best to keep track of distance, or take a bearing to verify if the trail you’ve found points the direction you expect.\nCourse Close: Please return to the download tent at start/finish by 1:30pm. You’ll lose points for every minute late. Wear a watch and come back on time!","external_links":[{"link_url":"https://goo.gl/maps/D6Xz52cRnUB2","link_type":"directions"},{"link_url":"https://goo.gl/maps/vhSueLWnoGn","link_type":"directions"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/event/ultimate-orienteer-7-score-o-2017/","link_type":"event_page"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/map/teanaway-valley/","link_type":"map"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/result/ultimate-series-6-pig-war-classic-lick-creek/","link_type":"related_result"},{"link_url":"http://rg.cascadeoc.org/rg2/#178","link_type":"routegadget"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/series/ultimate-orienteer/","link_type":"series"},{"link_url":"http://cascadeoc.org/result/ultimate-series-7-score-o-teanaway/#splits","link_type":"splits"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/season/ultimate-season-standings-17/","link_type":"standings"}],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Course Designer","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-7807-bdc6-77a7e939a3ae","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Eric Jones","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Epunch Coordinator","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-7807-bdc6-77a7e939a3ae","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Eric Jones","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Meet Director","individual_id":"019b815e-cce3-782c-b020-2b625672abe6","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Robert Stratton","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"CascadeOC Website: https://www.cascadeoc.org/result/ultimate-series-7-score-o-teanaway/","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club"}
